CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 16, 1965, pg. 7 reads: "Alpha Officers - At the last meeting of Alpha Omicron Lambda Chapter, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity installed the officers who will serve for the year 1965. At a social gathering held in Pick-Roosevelt Hotel, officers of Alpha Wives also were installed.  Atty. Wendell Freeland installed the officers of the fraternity.  Left to right: Dr. Woodford A. (Woody) Harris, president; William A.G. Fisher, vice president; Wilbur C. Douglass, secretary; John A. Cundieff, assistant secretary; Nathan Page (standing in for William Dorsay, sergeant-at-arms); Henry D. (Pro) McCullough, treasurer, and the Rev. LeRoy Patrick, chaplain.  Howard Hairston was chairman...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity officers, from left: Dr. Woodford A. "Woody" Harris, William A. G. Fisher, Wilbur C. Douglass, John A. Cundieff, Nathan Page (standing in for William Dorsey), Henry D. "Pro" McCullough, and Rev. LeRoy Patrick, standing in Pick - Roosevelt Hotel
